    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Doesn't it meet the spec? The core tells us that the new RPC has a really, really, really far-in-the-future deadline. [The core doesn't formally support semantics of \"if the deadline `gpr_timespec` value passed to you is equal to the `gpr_timespec` value returned by `gpr_inf_future`, consider the RPC to have no deadline\"](https://github.com/grpc/grpc/issues/9423). Nothing about the spec of `time_remaining` says that implementations must return `None` instead of a certain really, really far-in-the-future deadline value.\r\n\r\nSince the behavior drafted in this changelist isn't a regression, let's punt on this point?\r\n\r\nThanks for pointing out the existence of `__float__`."
  },
